history.content: You need to ask all these questions of the STAT department because CompSci and STAT often manage enrollment for this class differently. STAT does not monitor the EECS 101 forum. I have already answered question 4 for you privately/

I want to take C200A (I'm in other department graduate program), and there are several confusing parts.
1. The F19 enrollment guide says this semester enrollment of this course is through stat department. Then does everyone have to apply through STAT C100 or STAT C200? (not CS C200?)
2. Can other department graduate student take C100A instead of C200A, if C100A has available seats whereas C200A does not?
3. C200A on calcentral requires permission numbers. Where can I get those?

Thank you!
